{"type":"message","id":"ad56be19","parentId":"287f4ad5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:37:58.952Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. I found the wiki node. The space_id is `7615846908665285857` and the parent node token is `MVjqwq2pGi8GVKkXOn0c9VpNnTc`. I need to create a sub-node (document) under this parent node.\n\nNow I have the knowledge I need to write the document. Let me compile information about 12+ prompt frameworks and create a comprehensive MD document.\n\nHere are the prompt frameworks I'll cover:\n1. **APE** (Action, Purpose, Expectation) - by Mario Lyioc\n\n\n2. **TAG** (Task, Actor, Goal) - by Anthropic/Matt N\n3. **CoSTAR** (Context, Objective, Style, Task, Audience, Response)\n4. **RISE** (Role, Instructions, Steps, End Goal)\n5. **ICIO** (Instruction, Context, Input format, Output format)\n6. **CRISPE** (Capacity, Role, Insight, Statement, Personality, Experiment)\n7. **BROOKE** (Background, Role, Objective, Output, Process, Expectations)\n8. **ROSES** (Role, Objective, Style, Expec\n\nI'm continuing to compile the remaining frameworks including ROSES, along with several others like SCOPE, PAPRIKA, and theastes framework to ensure comprehensive coverage.","thinkingSignature":"2fdf3a85f6833edb372818e96929c2322876c979f19b8cad675a96ed197b24e1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4c3r07qfp38f_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://www.vapi.com/blog/prompt-engineering-frameworks","maxChars":20000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4c3r07qfp38f_2","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://eng.testgrid.io/blog/prompt-engineering-frameworks","maxChars":20000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-cn","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":3788,"output":373,"cacheRead":37026,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41187,"cost":{"input":0.0022727999999999997,"output":0.0008952,"cacheRead":0.0022215599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00538956}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1